definition.value: The context of the assessment establishing its purpose, the organisation of criteria being evaluated, and its reference frameworks.
A resource, probably resulting from a work, with purpose and value.
A value judgement, resulting from the assessment, pertinent to its entirety or to one or more of its specific parts.
The intellectual work to evaluate an asset against the criteria of a given scenario.

The context for a criterion providing guidance on its evaluation considering the given scenario. This is used exceptionally to extend the context offered by the scenario when it is not sufficient for the evaluation of a given criterion. An criterion's evaluation produces an objective output that will then be considered to form value judgments expressed as the assessment's statements.
The value output assigned to the criteria as part of the assessment.
Date of formal issuance of the Specification.
The previous version of a resource in a lineage.
A link to any information supporting the value of the asset and any other related relevant details.
The link to the scenario that provides the evaluation context for one or more criteria.
The categorisation of the statement.
The link to the evaluation contexts for specific criteria provided by the given scenario.
The evaluation of an assessment score as input to issue one or more statements.
The version indicator (name or identifier) of a resource.
The agent providing a score for a given criterion as part of the assessment.
The agent(s) that issue value judgement(s) resulting from the assessment.
The agent(s) that carry out the assessment.
The different resources provided to feed the context for the evaluation of a criterion.
Brief description of the resource.
The agent(s) requesting the assessment of an asset.
The reason for which the assessment is done.
The context for a criterion related to a resource.
The favourability perception of the statement (e.g. positive, negative or neutral).
Brief description of the Asset.
The assignment of a value output to the criterion.
The reference to the asset(s) that are the object of the assessment.
The text expressing the statement’s resulting value judgement.
The status of the Asset in the context of a particular workflow process.
The definition of nested scenarios grouped based on different sub-purposes, commonalities or particularities of the sub-sets of criteria.
The agent assigning the score for a given criterion as part of the assessment.
An abbreviated manifestation of the performed assessment.
The consideration of a specific evaluation context when assigning the score to a criterion.
The literal representing the score assigned.
The event causing the current assessment as the result of another related assessment.
The aggregation of criteria to one scenario or parts of it.
Date of formal issuance (e.g., publication) of the Specification.
Guideline or description that needs to followed during the evaluation of one particular criterion.
The creation of the statements resulting from the assessment.
A contact point for a person or organisation.
A manifestation of all the information related to and resulting from an assessment.
The event causing further related assessment(s) due to the current one.
The provision of context for the evaluation of the criterion.
The assignment of the scenario for the current assessment providing its context, purpose and criteria.
The provision of a value judgement on one or more elements of the assessment.
A name given to the resource.
